@reminisce @piiswrong @bhavinthaker
See original PR + code review: https://github.com/eric-haibin-lin/mxnet/pull/173

This PR including new features to export animations in glTF format.

### FEATURES

* added Makefiles to `.gitignore`.
* The `animations` dictionary is fully implemented to export animation of `nodes`.
* The `skins`dictionary is nearly finished, however not working correctly.
 * Since there are still issues,  I comment out the code to `ExportSkin`.
 * I believe that the joint nodes still need to be traced through correctly.

In `glTFExporter.cpp`
lines: 560 -564
```
    /*************** Skins ****************/
    ///TODO: Fix skinning animation
    // if(aim->HasBones()) {
    //     ExportSkin(*mAsset, aim, m, b);
    // }
```

### ISSUES
* Hard-coded `bindShapeMatrix` to be the identity for skins. This is temporary.

```
        // Identity Matrix   =====>  skinRef->bindShapeMatrix
        // Temporary. Hard-coded identity matrix here
        skinRef->bindShapeMatrix.isPresent = true;
        IdentityMatrix4(skinRef->bindShapeMatrix.value);
```

* Skins are temporarily disabled.


### NOTES
* Be aware that node names can be changed when exported since top level dictionary entries must have unique names. This is an issue for nodes since they are referenced in other places such as skins.
 * To fix this I switched the order so that `nodes` are exported before `meshes`.
* I made a `static void IdentityMatrix4(glTF::mat4& o)` function in `glTFExporter.cpp`. Does one exist somewhere else in to code so it does not need to be duplicated?


### TESTS

I tested using `robot.dae` and `glTF/sampleModels/BoxAnimated`.
[robot.zip](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/files/515515/robot.zip)
[BoxAnimated.dae.zip](https://github.com/assimp/assimp/files/515517/BoxAnimated.dae.zip)

Public headers are now available via:                                         

        #include <brotli/decode.h>
        #include <brotli/encode.h>
        #include <brotli/types.h>
                                                                                      
        #include <brotli/compressor.h>
        #include <brotli/streams.h>

The exposure of "types.h" (which is only useful for MSVC builds) is
a bit unfortunate, but this change would be much bigger without it.

Makefile tested with: make, BUILD file tested with: ngx_brotli,
Premake5 is broken (but it was broken before this change).

Closes: https://github.com/nteract/nteract/issues/1574

This currently depends on a pending PR on ipython: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/10404

Usage:

```py
GeoJSON(data={
    "type": "Feature",
    "geometry": {
        "type": "Point",
        "coordinates": [11.8, -45.04]
    }
}, url_template="http://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/whereonmars.cartodb.net/{basemap_id}/{z}/{x}/{y}.png", 
layer_options={
    "basemap_id": "mola-color",
    "attribution" : "NASA/MOLA",
    "tms": True,
    "minZoom" : 0,
    "maxZoom" : 6
})
```

